izes the various tensions inherent in the relationship. Grounded in economic means, racial and ethnic affiliation, and the contestation for space, sport is seen as precipitating a broad range of human challenges.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aCity and town life. 0aSportsxSocial aspects. 4aGeneral Interest : General Interest. 7aSPORTS & RECREATION / General.2bisacsh1 aAmbrose, Darren, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAndrews, David L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAndrews, David L., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aAtkinson, Michael F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBurd, Gene, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aClark, Michael A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCole, CL, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIngham, Alan G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIrwin, Richard L., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKing, Samantha, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMathy, Robin M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcDonald, Mary G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPitter, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPitter, Robert, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRiess, Steven A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRosenberg, Danny, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSlowikowski, Synthia Sydnor, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aThornton, Andrew D., econtr